description:
&lt;p&gt;This is a pivotal role that will be responsible for part of our recruitment team. You will need to be extremely well organised, work in a methodical manner and have relevant recruitment experience along with staff management. Any advert writing expertise would be desirable. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be highly professional, with a customer-centred, problem solving approach, confident communicator with the ability to establish and maintain excellent working relationships with a wide range of colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A flexible and pragmatic approach to your work and exceptional organisational skills that will enable you to manage a varied workload, with competing priorities and deadlines, is also key success in this role. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In return we are committed to providing on-going support, training and development and the opportunity to learn from experienced HR practitioners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For non-NHS applicants, starting salary will be based on number of years equivalent experience in a similar role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provisional virtual interview date: 18th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Also note that those who are successfully shortlisted will be asked to a complete an unseen exercise. Those who are successful will be invited to the virtual interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: Shereen Ratnabal, Job title: Recruitment Manager, Email address: shereen.ratnabal@nhs.net (no CV&#39;s please)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alternatively email: andrew.sims4@nhs.net or miriam.bone1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
